 by addressing imaginative, aesthetic, and epistemological questions. She analyzes how literature, psychoanalysis and the performing arts traverse and react to the ambivalence of racialized stereotypes. The »femininity puzzle« presents itself in two ways: first in the role of effeminization of the male Jew in antisemitic discourse, and then in the transgressive forms of femininity connected to Jewish women, especially the allosemitic orientalization in the figure of the »Beautiful Jewess«.  afunded by Backlisttransformation EOSC Future  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aFemininity-History. 0aFemininity. 4aAllosemitism. 4aAntisemitism. 4aBeautiful Jewess. 4aCultural History. 4aEffeminization. 4aEuropean History. 4aFreud. 4aGender History. 4aGender Studies. 4aHistory. 4aJewish Studies. 4aJudaism. 4aSalome. 4aSexology. 4aSociety. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh  aAllosemitism.  aAntisemitism.  aBeautiful Jewess.  aCultural History.  aEffeminization.  aEuropean History.  aFreud.  aGender History.  aGender Studies.  aHistory.  aJewish Studies.  aJudaism.  aSalome.  aSexology.  aSociety.2 aBacklisttransformation EOSC Futureefunder.4fnd4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/fnd08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2022 Part 2z978311076700108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2022 Englishz978311099296008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2